This paper is likely to belong to the Computational Linguistics (cs.CL) sub-category as it deals with the task of clickbait detection in Twitter tweets, which involves natural language processing. It could also belong to the Information Retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category as the task involves retrieving relevant information from tweets. Additionally, the paper involves feature selection and classification, which are common topics in the Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Finally, since the paper deals with clickbait detection, which is a form of online fraud, it could also belong to the Cryptography and Security (cs.CR) sub-category.
